> Have you checked your brake booster lately? I once had one filling  
> up with water, meaning that the brakes would not completely  
> retract. Each application of the brakes brought them a little  
> closer to the rotors (like a ratchet process). In the end (after  
> 200 miles) I had one red hot brake rotor ...
>
> Two ways of checking for this: once your bus starts pulling, can  
> you manually pull up the brake pedal (i.e. does it not return to  
> the highest point)? (2) Pull the vacuum hose and check whether  
> there is any fluid that you can siphon out. Mine was water, not  
> brake fluid - no idea how it got in there.
>
> Marcus
